Uses of Package
org.cloudbus.cloudsim.schedulers.vm

  • Packages that use org.cloudbus.cloudsim.schedulers.vm 
    Package Description
    org.cloudbus.cloudsim.hosts
    Provides Host implementations that represent a Physical Machine (PM) is used to run Vm from different cloud customers (represented by a DatacenterBroker).
    org.cloudbus.cloudsim.hosts.network
    Provides network-enabled Host implementations.
    org.cloudbus.cloudsim.hosts.power
    Provides power-aware Host implementations.
    org.cloudbus.cloudsim.schedulers.vm
    Provides VmScheduler implementations that are used to schedule the execution of multiple Vm inside a given Host.
    org.cloudsimplus.builders
    Provides Builder classes that implement the Builder Design Pattern to allow instantiating multiple simulation objects more easily.
  • Classes in org.cloudbus.cloudsim.schedulers.vm used by org.cloudbus.cloudsim.hosts 
    Class and Description
    VmScheduler
    An interface to be implemented by VmScheduler objects in order to provide scheduling algorithms that allocate host's PEs for VMs running on it.
  • Classes in org.cloudbus.cloudsim.schedulers.vm used by org.cloudbus.cloudsim.hosts.network 
    Class and Description

  • Classes in org.cloudbus.cloudsim.schedulers.vm used by org.cloudbus.cloudsim.schedulers.vm 
    Class and Description
    VmScheduler
    An interface to be implemented by VmScheduler objects in order to provide scheduling algorithms that allocate host's PEs for VMs running on it.
    VmSchedulerAbstract
    VmSchedulerAbstract is an abstract class that represents the policy used by a Virtual Machine Monitor (VMM) to share processing power of a PM among VMs running in a host.
    VmSchedulerTimeShared
    VmSchedulerTimeShared is a Virtual Machine Monitor (VMM) allocation policy that allocates one or more PEs from a PM to a VM, and allows sharing of PEs by multiple VMs.
  • Classes in org.cloudbus.cloudsim.schedulers.vm used by org.cloudsimplus.builders
